# ThreatForge Output — SIGNATURES
# CVE:       CVE-2026-56164
# Product:   sharepoint_server
# Tags:      [KEV] [RCE] [POC]
# Score:     100
# Tier:      CRITICAL — ACT NOW
# Generated: 2026-07-22T03:18:56.863728Z
# Status:    OK
# ---

# Confidence: PoC known — public proof-of-concept exists [7]; advisory
# detail from Resecurity [5] and Check Point [4] confirms unauthenticated
# HTTP-based privilege escalation against SharePoint endpoints. However,
# NO packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline —
# this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic. The
# content and PCRE matches below target generic unauthenticated access
# patterns on SharePoint API/authentication paths consistent with a
# missing-authentication-for-critical-function class of vulnerability
# (CWE-306). Specific request paths used by the PoC were not extractable
# from the available advisory text; pattern is inferred from CVE
# description [1][6], CISA KEV entry [3], and advisory titles [5].
# Analyst MUST review and validate match logic against actual exploit
# traffic or PoC source [7] before deployment. Do NOT deploy to IPS
# blocking mode without validation.
#
# SEVERITY DISCREPANCY NOTE: The NVD CVSS score for CVE-2026-56164 is
# 5.3 (MEDIUM) [1], yet the vulnerability is actively exploited in the
# wild per both CISA KEV (added 2026-07-14) [3] and VulnCheck KEV
# (added 2026-07-14) [2], with confirmed RCE via network-exploitable
# AV:N/PR:N/UI:N vector and a public PoC [7]. The MEDIUM CVSS score is
# likely an underrepresentation of operational risk. Analysts should
# treat this as CRITICAL priority consistent with the KEV listing and
# Priority Tier assigned by ThreatForge. Do not use the CVSS score alone
# to deprioritise response.
#
# THIS RULE IS A PROPOSED DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW.
alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-56164 Microsoft SharePoint missing auth privilege escalation attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.uri; content:"/_api/"; nocase;
  pcre:"/\/_api\/(web|site|contextinfo|lists|siteusers|SP\.UserProfiles)/i";
  http.header; content:!"Authorization"; nocase;
  content:!"Cookie"; nocase;
  threshold:type both, track by_src, count 5, seconds 60;
  reference:cve,2026-56164;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev true, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-admin; sid:9000164; rev:1; )

